biolockj.module.implicit.parser

Class ParserModuleImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • biolockj.module.BioModuleImpl
      • biolockj.module.ScriptModuleImpl
        • biolockj.module.JavaModuleImpl
          • biolockj.module.implicit.parser.ParserModuleImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BioModule, ParserModule, JavaModule, ScriptModule
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    KrakenParser, MetaphlanParser, QiimeParser, RdpParser, SlimmParser

    public abstract class ParserModuleImpl
extends JavaModuleImpl
implements ParserModule
    Parser BioModules read ClassifierModule output to build standardized OTU abundance tables. This class provides the default abstract implementation.

      • REPORT_MINIMUM_OTU_COUNT

        protected static final String REPORT_MINIMUM_OTU_COUNT
        Config property "report.minOtuCount" defines the minimum OTU count that will be added to the raw count table. A sample will only include an OTU if the count meets or exceeds this value.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • REPORT_MINIMUM_OTU_THRESHOLD

        protected static final String REPORT_MINIMUM_OTU_THRESHOLD
        Config property "report.minOtuThreshold" defines the total across all samples an OTU must reach to be included in the raw count table. OTUs that do not reach the threshold, will be omitted.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • runModule

        public void runModule()
               throws Exception
        Parsers execute a task with 3 core functions:
        1. parseSamples() - generates ParsedSamples
        2. buildOtuCounts() - stores internal summary counts for the ParsedSamples
        3. registerNumHits() (if Config."report.numHits" = "Y")
        4. buildOtuTables() - builds output tables
        Specified by:
        runModule in interface JavaModule
        Specified by:
        runModule in class JavaModuleImpl
        Throws:
        Exception - thrown if any runtime error occurs

      • isValid

        protected boolean isValid(OtuNode node)
        Some ClassifierModules can include taxonomy level identifiers without an OTU name in the sample report files. This method verifies the node exists, has a valid sample ID, and that no emptry String OTU names are reported.
        Parameters:
        node - OtuNode build from 1 line of a ClassifierModule output file
        Returns:
        boolean if OtuNode is valid
